---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Sunil Mayya — software engineer at Mozilla, working on Firefox."
	pubDate={new Date('June 28 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		I'm Sunil Mayya, a software engineer at Mozilla working on Firefox —
		primarily the web platform, networking, and media. Day to day that means
		implementing web-platform features in Gecko and taking part in the standards
		conversations (WICG, IETF, W3C) that shape them.
	</p>

	<p>
		A lot of my recent work sits at the boundary between the browser and the
		network: things like
		<a href="https://wicg.github.io/local-network-access/">Local Network Access</a>,
		HTTP caching, and the media stack. I enjoy the parts of the job that don't
		make it into the release notes — the design tradeoffs, the cross-vendor
		disagreements, and the implementation details you only discover once you try
		to ship the thing.
	</p>

	<p>
		I write here about that work — browser internals and web standards explained
		from the inside. Away from the editor I spend a fair bit of time in the
		kitchen, so you'll also find cooking recipes here, alongside the occasional
		post about life in general.
	</p>

	<p>
		You can reach me at <a href="mailto:smayya@mozilla.com">smayya@mozilla.com</a>.
		I do most of my work in the open; you'll find my contributions on
		<a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/">Bugzilla</a> and across Mozilla's
		<a href="https://github.com/mozilla">GitHub</a>.
	</p>

	<p>
		<em>The opinions on this site are my own and don't necessarily represent
		those of Mozilla.</em>
	</p>
</Layout>
